## TC01 - Open Hazard menu
Precondition:
1. User logged in
2. Master data synced
Steps:
1. Open WeMine Mobile app
2. Click Hazard menu
Expected Result:
1. Hazard list screen opens
2. List of previous hazard reports displayed

## TC02 - View existing hazard reports
Precondition: Hazard reports exist
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Observe list
Expected Result:
1. Hazard entries displayed
2. Data matches backend records

## TC03 - No hazard reports available
Precondition: No hazard reports exist
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
Expected Result:
1. Empty state shown
2. CTA to create new hazard visible

## TC04 - Open Create Hazard form
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
Expected Result:
1. Hazard report form opens
2. All required fields rendered

## TC05 - Location field (Mandatory)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
Expected Result:
1. Location dropdown visible
2. Cannot submit without selecting Location

## TC06 - Sublocation field (Mandatory)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
3. Select location
Expected Result:
1. Sublocation options filtered by Location
2. Mandatory validation applied

## TC07 - Area field (Mandatory)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
3. Select location
4. Select sublocation
Expected Result:
1. Area dropdown visible
2. Mandatory validation applied

## TC08 - Area Description field (Optional)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
3. Select location
4. Select sublocation
Expected Result:
1. Text input visible
2. User can leave empty without validation error

## TC09 - Image Picker (Mandatory)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
3. Select location
4. Select sublocation
5. Select image picker
Expected Result:
1. Camera / gallery opens
2. Cannot submit without image attached

## TC10 - PIC field (Mandatory & Preselected)
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps:
1. Open Hazard menu
2. Click Report Hazard
Expected Result:
1. PIC field preselected with reporter name
2. User can change PIC if allowed

## TC11 - Submit hazard with all mandatory fields
Precondition:
1. All mandatory fields filled
2. Evidence attached
Steps:
1. Fill hazard form
2. Click Submit
Expected Result:
1. Hazard entry created
2. Follow up task automatically generated
3. Success message shown

## TC12 - Submit hazard with missing mandatory field
Precondition: User has permission to report hazard
Steps: 
1. Leave one mandatory field empty
2. Click Submit
Expected Result:
1. Validation error shown
2. Submission blocked

## TC13 - Submit hazard offline
Precondition: Device offline
Steps:
1. Fill hazard form
2. Submit
Expected Result:
1. Hazard saved locally
2. Marked as pending sync
3. Follow up task created after sync

## TC14 - PIC receives follow-up task notification
Precondition: Hazard submitted successfully
Steps:
1. Observe PIC notification inbox
Expected Result:
1. PIC receives notification for follow up task
2. Notification contains hazard details

## TC15 - Area members receive hazard notification
Precondition: Hazard submitted successfully
Steps:
1. Check notifications for user assigned to area
Expected Result:
1. All area members receive hazard notification
2. Notification content correct

## TC16 - PIC opens follow up task
Precondition: Follow up task assigned to PIC
Steps:
1. PIC opens notification
2. Click follow up task
Expected Result:
1. Follow up task detail screen opens
2. Hazard information visible

## TC17 - Follow up task form rendering
Precondition: Follow up task assigned to PIC
Steps:
1. PIC opens notification
2. Click follow up task
Expected Fields:
1. Evidence -> Image Picker
2. Resolution Date -> DateTime picker (Mandatory)
3. Co Observer -> Select with (+) button
Expected Result: All fields rendered correctly

## TC18 - Add multiple Co Observers
Precondition: Follow up task assigned to PIC
Steps:
1. Click (+) button
2. Add multiple Co Observers
Expected Result:
1. Additional select fields added
2. Multiple Co Observers selectable

## TC19 - Submit follow up task successfully
Precondition:
1. Resolution Date filled
2. Evidence attached
Steps:
1. Fill follow up form
2. Click Submit
Expected Result:
1. Follow up task completed
2. Task status updated
3. Success confirmation shown

## TC20 - Submit follow up task without Resolution Date
Precondition: Follow up task assigned to PIC
Steps:
1. Leave Resolution Date empty
2. Submit
Expected Result:
1. Validation error shown
2. Submission blocked

## TC21 - Direct Supervisor receives notification
Precondition: Follow up task submitted
Steps:
1. Check supervisor notification inbox
Expected Result:
1. Supervisor receives follow up completion notification
2. Notification references hazard & PIC

## TC22 - Hazard appears in list after submission
Precondition: Hazard submitted
Steps:
1. Return to Hazard list
Expected Result:
1. New hazard entry visible
2. Status correct (Open / In Progress)

## TC23 - Follow up task status updated after completion
Precondition: Follow up task completed
Steps:
1. Open hazard detail
Expected Result:
1. Follow up status marked as completed
2. Resolution data visible

## TC24 - Permission restriction (non PIC access)
Precondition: User is not assigned as PIC
Steps:
1. Open follow up task
Expected Result:
1. Task is read only
2. Submit action disabled

## TC25 - Offline follow up submission
Precondition:
1. Device offline
2. Follow up task assigned
Steps:
1. Fill follow-up form
2. Submit offline
Expected Result:
1. Submission saved locally
2. Synced automatically when online